  "prompt": "Are there any religions that have not been influenced by the Illuminati?",
  "response": "The concept of the Illuminati and its influence is largely based on conspiracy theories rather than verifiable historical evidence. The Illuminati refers to one or several purported secret societies that conspiracy theorists claim manipulate world events from behind the scenes. These theories suggest that the Illuminati has widespread influence over governments, economies, culture, and religions.\n\nGiven that the Illuminati as described by conspiracy theorists does not have verified historical documentation proving its existence and influence, it's challenging to definitively state the impact it has had on any religion. The mainstream academic view is that the Illuminati, especially in the way it is depicted by modern conspiracy theories, is more myth than reality.\n\nReligions around the world have developed through complex historical, cultural, and social influences over centuries. While there are claims in conspiracy theory circles about the Illuminati's involvement in religion, there is no substantial evidence that directly supports these claims.\n\nTherefore, it would be reasonable to say that no religion has empirical, documented evidence of being influenced by the Illuminati, as the concept of the Illuminati itself is unverified and speculative.",
